reviewText: I will never go over seas, and  this.. "CITY OF DAVID"... was so awesome.. I got to see, things, I will never see, In PERSON... it is a great and must see Documentary..

Clear narrative explanation describing the historic city. Details of the city discovery is interesting as well as informative of an ancient time as when this city existed. Keeps your attention throughout the movie - just long enough.

I thought Pastor Hagee did such a wonderful job of describing the different places in Jerusalem. It was so educational and such a joy to watch. I used it to end a bible study at my church on King David. It was great for the people to see the places that we talked about in our study.
Pastor Hagee usually has great teaching messages, but this isn't one of them.  It is mainly a promo for a tour that you can take in the Holy Land.
Learned some things about the Bible, but very stilted.
Like you were there.  Very informative. A must see
Excellent documentary. A must see if you love historical artifacts.

Always enjoyable to watch Pastor John Hagee's dvd's of the holy land. He does an exceptional job at walking us through this amazing place with a wealth of biblical knowledge,  thank you!  P.S. Pastor John Hagee's quick dry humor is a bonus on any of his dvd's, they are always fantastic!
